---++ Dave Dykstra - Technology: OASIS

   1 I am working on an update to OASIS including 17 tickets, to be put into production end of March or April.  11 done, 1 almost done, 5 more to go.  I hope to have them done by next week.
   1 These are the most significant changes:
      1 Upgrade oasis and oasis-repiica to cvmfs-server-2.2.X.  The oasis-replica update is needed in order to support osgstorage.org repositories, a new feature for auxiliary data storage from Brian in cvmfs-2.2.X client that integrates with StashCache.
      1 Add a configuration repository.  Shared configuration can be updated centrally.  Most important is to be able to centrally add to a &quot;blacklist&quot; for security emergencies.  Will include use of this with all cvmfs-2.2.X clients.
